## Issue Description
Cross-chain operations lack timeout mechanisms, risking stuck transactions.

## Timeout Requirements
- Configurable timeout per operation
- Automatic refund on timeout
- Status tracking
- Extension capability

## Implementation
```rust
pub struct CrossChainOp {
    pub id: BytesN<32>,
    pub deadline: u64,
    pub refund_address: Address,
}

pub fn check_timeout(env: Env, op_id: BytesN<32>) -> Result<(), Error> {
    let op = Self::get_operation(&env, op_id)?;
    if env.ledger().timestamp() > op.deadline {
        Self::refund(&env, op)?;
    }
}
```

## Default Timeouts
- Token transfer: 1 hour
- Message passing: 30 minutes
- Verification: 15 minutes

## Issue Description
Inconsistent initialization patterns across contracts.

## Standard Pattern
```rust
pub fn initialize(
    env: Env,
    admin: Address,
    // other config
) -> Result<(), Error> {
    if Self::is_initialized(&env) {
        return Err(Error::AlreadyInitialized);
    }

    admin.require_auth();

    // Set initial state
    env.storage().persistent().set(&DataKey::Admin, &admin);
    env.storage().persistent().set(&DataKey::Initialized, &true);

    env.events().publish(("initialized",), admin);
    Ok(())
}
```

## Requirements
- Single initialization enforcement
- Admin authentication
- Event emission
- State validation

## Testing
- Double initialization prevention
- Invalid admin rejection
- State verification after init

## Issue Description
Contracts may be vulnerable to reentrancy attacks in payment flows.

## Vulnerable Patterns
- External calls before state updates
- Recursive function calls
- Cross-contract interactions

## Fix Implementation
```rust
// Use mutex pattern
pub fn withdraw(env: Env, amount: i128) -> Result<(), Error> {
    let mut balance = Self::get_balance(&env)?;

    // Update state FIRST
    balance -= amount;
    env.storage().persistent().set(&DataKey::Balance, &balance);

    // Then external call
    Self::transfer_tokens(&env, amount)?;

    Ok(())
}
```

## Audit Checklist
- [ ] State updates before external calls
- [ ] Reentrancy guards implemented
- [ ] Cross-contract call analysis
- [ ] Testing for reentrancy scenarios

## Issue Description
Inconsistent authorization patterns across contract functions.

## Standard Pattern
```rust
pub fn update_profile(
    env: Env,
    provider: Address,
    data: ProfileData
) -> Result<(), Error> {
    // Require authentication
    provider.require_auth();

    // Verify ownership
    if !Self::is_owner(&env, &provider) {
        return Err(Error::Unauthorized);
    }

    // Execute operation
}
```

## Requirements
- Always call `require_auth()`
- Verify permissions
- Emit auth events
- Handle auth failures gracefully

## Audit
- Review all public functions
- Add missing auth checks
- Test auth bypass scenarios
- Document auth requirements

## Issue Description
No documented patterns for contract-to-contract interaction.

## Composition Patterns
### Factory Pattern
```rust
pub fn create_instance(env: Env, config: Config) -> Address {
    // Deploy new contract instance
}
```

### Registry Pattern
```rust
pub fn register_contract(env: Env, address: Address, metadata: Metadata) {
    // Track contract in registry
}
```

### Adapter Pattern
```rust
pub fn adapt_interface(env: Env, data: ExternalData) -> InternalData {
    // Convert between contract interfaces
}
```

## Documentation Needed
- Pattern descriptions
- Use cases
- Code examples
- Anti-patterns to avoid

## Testing
- Integration test suites
- Mock contract implementations
- Composition validation
